All older research on the subject was strongly influenced by the theory of a systematic regulation of settlement at some unspecified time in the Late Iron Age. This theory originated in a history of Denmark written by Erik Arup in 1925 and has since appeared intermittently in archaeological literature. One example is G.Hatt’s work of 1937, where the difference between the village types of the Early Iron Age and the Middle Ages was explained as a result of a state initiative about the middle of the first millennium AD.
